{{Unreferenced|date=October 2009}}
[[Brunei]] is in [[Southeastern Asia]], bordering the [[South China Sea]] and [[Malaysia]].  Its geographical coordinates are {{Coord|4|30|N|114|40|E|}}.

Brunei shares a {{convert|481.3|km|mi|abbr=on}} [[Brunei-Malaysia Border|border]] with Malaysia and has a {{convert|161|km|mi|abbr=on}} coastline.

== Climate ==
{{See also|Brunei#Climate|l1=Climate}}

The [[climate]] in Brunei is [[tropical climate|tropical]] [[Tropical rainforest climate|equatorial]] and [[humid subtropical]] at higher altitudes with heavy rainfall. Bandar Seri Begawan's climate is tropical equatorial with two seasons. Dry season is extremely hot ({{convert|24|to|36|C|F|1|abbr=on|disp=or}}. Wet or rainy season is generally warm and wet ({{convert|20|to|28|C|F|1|abbr=on|disp=or}}). Most of the country is a flat [[coastal plain]] with [[mountain]]s in the east and hilly lowland in the west.  The lowest point is at [[sea level]] and the highest is [[Bukit Pagon]] ({{convert|1850|m|ft|0|abbr=on|disp=or}}).

=== Climatic regions ===
*[[Brunei-Muara District]] and [[Bandar Seri Begawan]] are humid tropical on the coastal and lower altitude north and Humid subtropical in central Brunei-Muara District. ({{convert|20|to|36|C|F|abbr=on|disp=or}})

*[[Tutong District]] is [[tropical]], Hot on the north and warm on the south. ({{convert|22|to|32|C|F|1|abbr=on|disp=or}})

*[[Belait District]] is tropical, Hot on the north and slight warm on the south. ({{convert|25|to|37|C|F|1|abbr=on|disp=or}})

*[[Temburong District]] is [[humid subtropical]] on the higher altitude south and humid tropical on the coastal and lower altitude north. ({{convert|18|to|29|C|F|abbr=on|disp=or}})

== Natural resources ==
Natural resources include [[petroleum]], [[natural gas]] and [[timber]].

